    "body" : "<p>While all the previous responses are correct, they're all in Java. Here's a Scala example:</p>\n\n<pre class=\"lang-scala prettyprint-override\"><code>val placeholder = \"Hello %s, isn't %s cool?\"\nval formatted = placeholder.format(\"Ivan\", \"Scala\")\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>I also have a blog post about <a href=\"http://www.bubblefoundry.com/blog/2010/06/fun-with-scala-implicits/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">making <code>format</code> like Python's <code>%</code> operator</a> that might be useful.</p>\n"
  }, {
