      "body" : "It is call String interpolation, within scala there are two types: s&quot;&quot; and f&quot;&quot;, the &#39;s&#39; is simple string and the &#39;f&#39; is similar to the <code>printf</code>, you could even define your own interpolation (I haven&#39;t try).  The <code>$name</code> means that it need to be replace with the value of the variable <code>name</code>, you could also do operation in the interpolation, for example <code>s&quot;Hello ${name.toUpperCase}, it&#39;s $weather today!&quot;</code>"
