    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>In scala , for string Interpolation we have <strong>$</strong> that saves the day and make our life much easy:</p>\n\n<p><strong>For Example:</strong> You want to define a function that takes input name and age and says Hello With the name and says its age.\nThat can be written like this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>def funcStringInterpolationDemo(name:String,age:Int)=s\"Hey ! my name is $name and my age is $age\"\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Hence , When you call this function: like this :</p>\n\n<pre><code>funcStringInterpolationDemo(\"Shivansh\",22)\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Its output would be :</p>\n\n<pre><code>Hey ! my name is Shivansh and my age is 22\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>You can write the code to change it in the same line, like if you want to add 10 years to the age ! </p>\n\n<p>then function could be :</p>\n\n<pre><code>def funcStringInterpolationDemo(name:String,age:Int)=s\"Hey ! my name is $name and my age is ${age+10}\"\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>And now the output would be :</p>\n\n<pre><code>Hey ! my name is Shivansh and my age is 32\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
